post_text: CPE has been collaborating with Community Dental Care for the last 6 years serving 1st, 2nd and 3rd grade students. Once a year, Community Dental Care comes to CPE to help clean students' teeth and apply dental seal. Before they start the dental care, they give the students a short presentation about how to keep their teeth clean and healthy. The students loved it and parents loved it as well.

post_text: CPE celebrated Character Day on October 31st. Students and staff dressed up as their favorite book character. Student Council went around each classroom and picked the best dressed. The first place winner went to Chazity in 6th grade as the Grandmother from Little Red Riding Hood. The second place winner went to Alijiah in 4th grade as the White Rabbit from Alice in Wonderland. The third place went to Meadow in 1st grade as Rapunzel. The staff winner was Ms. Grace, CPE's art teacher, who dressed as Arthur. Congratulations winners!
